sp.p:
A lord to a lord, a man to a man;
stuffed with
all honorable virtues.

My visor is Philemon's roof;
within the house
is Jove.

So would not I, for your own sake;
for I have
many ill qualities.

I would have sworn it had, my lord;
especially
against Benedick.

sp.l:
That only wounds by hearsay.
Enter BEATRICE, behind.

Now begin;

sp.p:
We will rather sleep than talk;
we know
what belongs to a watch.

These gloves the count sent me;
they are an
excellent perfume.

I will swear by it that you love me;
and I will
make him eat it that says I love not you.

Marry, sir, they have committed false
report;
moreover, they have spoken untruths;
secondarily, they
are slanders; sixth and
lastly, they have belied a lady;
thirdly, they
have verified unjust things; and, to conclude,
they are lying knaves.

Thy wit is as quick as the greyhound's
mouth;
it catches.
